ActCustoms Tariff
SubjectCUSMA Rules of Origin Regulations
PrecisCUSMA RULES OF ORIGIN REGULATIONS in order to implement the “Uniform Regulations Regarding the Interpretation, Application, and Administration of Chapter 4 (Rules of Origin) and Chapter 6 (Textiles and Apparel Goods),” a trilaterally negotiated document that includes all of the rules of origin negotiated in the Canada-United States-Mexico Agreement (CUSMA), as well as additional details to ensure that the rules of origin are uniformly interpreted and applied in Canada, the United States and Mexico.
